---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Preparatory Program">
	<h1>Preparatory Program</h1>

	<p>
		The Preparatory Program helps students master economic models through
		structured problem-solving. It is built for those preparing for the
		MS/PhD entrance examinations in Quantitative Economics at the Indian
		Statistical Institute (ISI), for the 2027 intake and beyond.
	</p>

	<h2>Who it's for</h2>
	<p>
		The program is primarily for students aiming at a master's or PhD in
		economics, particularly at ISI. Students already enrolled in master's or
		PhD programs have also found it useful — the foundations built here tend
		to keep paying off through graduate coursework and research.
	</p>

	<h2>What it covers</h2>
	<p>The syllabus spans the core areas tested in the entrance exam:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Microeconomics</li>
		<li>Macroeconomics</li>
		<li>Mathematics</li>
		<li>Probability</li>
		<li>Statistics</li>
		<li>Econometrics</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>How it works</h2>
	<dl class="details">
		<dt>Instructor</dt><dd>Amit Goyal</dd>
		<dt>Mode</dt><dd>Online, live lectures</dd>
		<dt>Language</dt><dd>English</dd>
		<dt>Start date</dt><dd>14 June 2026</dd>
		<dt>Schedule</dt><dd>About two 1.5-hour sessions per week</dd>
		<dt>Total instruction</dt><dd>Around 100 hours, live</dd>
		<dt>Fees</dt><dd>₹80,000</dd>
		<dt>Included</dt><dd>Integrated Test Series</dd>
	</dl>

	<h2>How to register</h2>
	<p>Registration for the 2027 batch is open.</p>
	<p><a href="https://rzp.io/rzp/prep2027">Register for the 2027 batch</a></p>
	<p>
		To hear about future batches, fill out the
		<a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSch1s6F22_cMfZaHPA-kAWIRmOf23J5ZK-w20-uPUdTqrpBGg/viewform">interest form</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>

<style>
	.details {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: max-content 1fr;
		gap: 0.4rem 1.5rem;
		margin: 1rem 0;
	}

	.details dt {
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--es-ink);
	}

	.details dd {
		margin: 0;
	}
</style>